# Browser actions

This folder contains extensions that help in performing certain browser actions inside your Virtuoso journey.

## Get local storage

**<u>Description</u>**: This extension allows you to retrieve values stored into the local storage using the setLocalStorage extension or that are stored into local storage by the web application itself.

**<u>How to Use</u>**:

1. Write a step: `localStorageGet (key)` returning **$var**.

2. `key` in this case will be the key of the data stored in the **localStorageSet** extension e.g. authcode.


**<u>Add to Virtuoso</u>**:

- <a href="https://app2.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=localStorageGet&org=true&" class="button big">Add to app2 (Free trial) env</a>
- <a href="https://app.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=localStorageGet&org=true&" class="button big">Add to app (Production) env</a>

## Set local storage

**<u>Description</u>**: This extension allows you to pass in a value to store in the browser local storage.

**<u>How to Use</u>**:

1. Write a step: `localStorageSet (key, value)`.
2. `key` in this case will be the variable name e.g. authcode and `value` will be the value you want to store e.g. 475923

**<u>Add to Virtuoso</u>**:

- <a href="https://app2.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=localStorageSet&org=true&%3D%3D" class="button big">Add to app2 (Free trial) env</a>
- <a href="https://app.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=localStorageSet&org=true&%3D%3D" class="button big">Add to app (Production) env</a>

## Blank tab

**<u>Description</u>**: This extension opens a new blank tab.

**<u>How to Use</u>**:

1. Write a step: `BlankTab`.
2. `Switch to tab <x>`.
3. Replace <x> with the **id** of the tab. If you have 2 tabs, it will be 1. If you have 3 tabs, it will be 2, for 4 tabs, it will be 3 and so on.

**<u>Add to Virtuoso</u>**:

- <a href="https://app2.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=BlankTab&org=true&%3D%3D" class="button big">Add to app2 (Free trial) env</a>
- <a href="https://app.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=BlankTab&org=true&%3D%3D" class="button big">Add to app (Production) env</a>

## Reload

**<u>Description</u>**: This extension reloads the current web page.

**<u>How to Use</u>**:

1. Write a step: `Reload`.
2. This will reload the active tab.

**<u>Add to Virtuoso</u>**:

- <a href="https://app2.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=Reload&org=true&%3D" class="button big">Add to app2 (Free trial) env</a>
- <a href="https://app.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=Reload&org=true&%3D" class="button big">Add to app (Production) env</a>

## Store URL

**<u>Description</u>**: This extension stores the URL of the current browser tab.

**<u>How to Use</u>**:

1. Write a step: `StoreURL returning $currenturl`.
2. This will save the URL of the active tab into the variable **$currentURL**.

**<u>Add to Virtuoso</u>**:

- <a href="https://app2.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=StoreURL&org=true&%3D%3D" class="button big">Add to app2 (Free trial) env</a>

- <a href="https://app2.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=StoreURL&org=true&%3D%3D" class="button big">Add to app (Production) env</a>
